task_description: Facing the building to your East (approx. 67°), estimate the height of the main building in front of you in meters. Answer with one number and a short rationale.

reason: To estimate the building's height, I need to see its full vertical extent; rotating up will reveal the roof while keeping the base visible for reference.
I need to reorient to face the target building at 67° east; rotating right by 67° will align my view with the building's direction for accurate height assessment.
I need to adjust the pitch upward to see the top of the building; rotating up by 60° will shift the view from 30° down to 30° up, revealing the full vertical extent for height estimation.
I must rotate right 67° to face the target building at 67°E and lower the pitch by 60° to align the view horizontally for accurate height estimation.
Adjusting pitch upward by 90° to shift from 60° down to 30° up, enabling full vertical view of the building for height estimation.
I need to rotate right 67° to face the target building and lower the pitch by 85° to align the view horizontally for accurate height estimation.
Rotating up 90° from 85° down will align the pitch to 5° up, enabling visibility of the building's roof while keeping the ground reference for height estimation.
I need to rotate right 67° to face the target building and lower the pitch by 85° to achieve a horizontal view for accurate height estimation.
Rotating up 90° from 85° down will position the pitch at 5° up, allowing simultaneous visibility of the building's base and roof for accurate height estimation.
After aligning the view to face the building at 67°E with a horizontal pitch, the building's height can be estimated as approximately 25 meters based on typical multi-story structure proportions.
